```

smaCross: signal at i: long when sma10 > sma40, was short - use prev cross
```javascript
onBar(bars, closes, i, holding) {
  const sf = sma(closes, i, 10);
  const ss = sma(closes, i, 40);
  if (sf == null || ss == null) return 'hold';
  const sf1 = sma(closes, i - 1, 10);
  const ss1 = sma(closes, i - 1, 40);
  if (sf1 == null) return 'hold';
  const bull = sf > ss;
  const bull1 = sf1 > ss1;
  if (bull && !bull1 && !holding) return 'buy';
  if (!bull && bull1 && holding) return 'sell';
  return 'hold';
}
```

Donchian: long when close >= max(high, 20), exit when close < min(low, 10) - simplified

```javascript
function donchianHigh(bars, i, n) {
  if (i < n - 1) return null;
  let h = -Infinity;
  for (let j = i - n + 1; j <= i; j++) h = Math.max(h, bars[j].h);
  return h;
}
function donchianLow(bars, i, n) {
  if (i < n - 1) return null;
  let l = Infinity;
  for (let j = i - n + 1; j <= i; j++) l = Math.min(l, bars[j].l);
  return l;
}
```

onBar: if !holding && closes[i] >= donchianHigh(bars, i-1, 20) - breakout uses PREVIOUS channel

Actually classic: enter when price breaks above prior 20-bar high (signal at close of bar when close > highest high of prior 20 excluding today or including?)

Use: at i, high20 = max high of [i-20, i-1], if close[i] > high20 buy

**RSI mean rev**: buy when RSI(i) < 32, sell when RSI(i) > 58 or bars since entry > 12

Need state for entry bar - use closure in factory

```javascript
function strategyRsi(bars, baseOpts, warm) {
  let entryBar = -999;
  return runLongFlat(bars, baseOpts, {
    warm,
    onBar(bars, closes, i, holding) {
      const r = rsi(closes, i, 14);
      if (r == null) return 'hold';
      if (!holding && r < 32) return 'buy';
      if (holding) {
        if (r > 58 || i - entryBar > 16) return 'sell';
      }
      return 'hold';
    },
  });
}
```
